02/11/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac said on Saturday (November 1st) that Serbia will have a fully professional army by 2010. In an interview in the latest issue of Odbrana magazine, Sutanovac acknowledged much work remains to achieve necessary reforms. 
In other news, Serbian customs officials found radioactive materials Friday in a cargo train travelling from the southern Serbian town of Dimitrovgrad to Macedonia. Radioactivity levels inside the specific carriage were 3,000 times higher than the limit. Dimitrovgrad customs chief Ivan Stoimenov confirmed the information and said the carriage was isolated and returned to Serbia. (Tanjug, Odbrana, B92, Blic, RTS, BNT, MIA, Netinfo, Darik - 01/11/08)
